# Natural Disasters & Voting Analysis Workflow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Input Data] --> B[Data Cleaning & Preparation]
    B --> C[Disaster Summarization]
    C --> D[Visualization]
    D --> E[Voting Analysis]
    E --> F[Spatial Mapping]
    F --> G[Interpretation & Reporting]

    %% Input Data
    A --> A1[FEMA Disaster Data]
    A --> A2[County & Census Data]
    A --> A3[Election Results (US, LA, CA)]

    %% Data Cleaning & Preparation
    B --> B1[Format dates & construct FIPS]
    B --> B2[Remove invalid/missing entries]

    %% Disaster Summarization
    C --> C1[Count disasters per county/year]
    C --> C2[Identify top 5 counties by total disasters]

    %% Visualization
    D --> D1[Total disasters in US by year (dot-line chart)]
    D --> D2[Top 5 counties by total disasters (bar chart)]
    D --> D3[Disasters by county: US map]
    D --> D4[Disasters by county: LA map]
    D --> D5[Disasters by county: CA map]

    %% Voting Analysis
    E --> E1[Process election results]
    E --> E2[Compare disasters to voter turnout (scatterplot)]

    %% Spatial Mapping
    F --> F1[Map US counties colored by total disasters]

    %% Interpretation & Reporting
    G --> G1[Summarize trends & prepare poster]
